==English==

===Etymology===
{{borrowing|fro|civilien|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/sɪˈvɪljən/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-civilian.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[person]] following the pursuits of [[civil]] life, especially one who is not an active member of the armed forces.
#: {{usex|Three '''civilians''' were apprehended by the soldiers and taken away in a military vehicle.|lang=en}}
# {{label|en|informal}}  A person who does not belong to a particular group or engage in a particular activity.
# One skilled in [[civil law]].
#* Jonathan Swift
#*: {{usex|Ancient '''civilians''' and writers upon government.|lang=en}}
# A [[student]] of [[civil law]] at a [[university]] or [[college]].
#: {{rfquotek|R. Graves}}

